WEBVTT

1
00:00:40.940 --> 00:00:43.340
This way.

2
00:01:00.420 --> 00:01:02.820
It's right here.

3
00:01:22.260 --> 00:01:24.460
Wait.

4
00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:50.860
It's all set. Don Minu.

5
00:01:50.940 --> 00:01:55.620
We're going to find
your grandson. don't worry.

6
00:02:20.940 --> 00:02:25.860
- Where could your grandfather be?
- I told you I don't know.

7
00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:31.180
You know my grandfather
doesn't trust anyone.

8
00:02:31.300 --> 00:02:34.460
There aren't many places
for him to hide.

9
00:02:51.380 --> 00:02:55.860
We can lay low here for a while.
I have a nice room for you.

10
00:02:55.940 --> 00:02:59.620
With a beautiful view.
What should we eat tonight?

11
00:03:01.500 --> 00:03:03.700
You think we're stupid?

12
00:03:03.780 --> 00:03:06.660
You think the Curtigas
are a family of idiots?

13
00:03:09.100 --> 00:03:13.540
You all have bad blood.
you. your father. your grandfather...

14
00:03:14.500 --> 00:03:18.300
Wait!
The ship didn't sink.

15
00:03:18.380 --> 00:03:21.980
The shipment's on its way. you hear me?

16
00:03:23.180 --> 00:03:24.300
Ah. really?

17
00:03:24.500 --> 00:03:28.660
My grandfather told me
the last time we saw each other.

18
00:03:38.940 --> 00:03:41.300
Get him.

19
00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:43.420
This way. c'mon.

20
00:07:01.340 --> 00:07:04.060
Wait. sweetheart.

21
00:07:07.100 --> 00:07:10.420
Duck down. go under.

22
00:07:15.060 --> 00:07:18.100
Scooch up a bit. good boy.

23
00:07:29.820 --> 00:07:33.620
- Good morning. Where's the lady?
- She's upstairs.

24
00:07:33.820 --> 00:07:37.340
Give me a hand?
Thank you. Come here.

25
00:07:40.220 --> 00:07:43.740
Straight ahead. into the courtyard.

26
00:07:46.460 --> 00:07:49.380
We're nearly there.

27
00:07:50.340 --> 00:07:54.260
- The lady? Thank you.
- She's upstairs.

28
00:07:57.740 --> 00:08:01.500
Domenico. hold on. we're nearly there.

29
00:08:05.540 --> 00:08:09.100
- Good morning. Where is she?
- In there.

30
00:08:09.300 --> 00:08:12.860
- Keep an eye on my kid. please.
- Come.

31
00:08:12.980 --> 00:08:16.180
- What's your name?
- Domenico.

32
00:08:23.180 --> 00:08:25.860
My respects.

33
00:08:39.060 --> 00:08:44.660
- The Lord helps you.
- He helps for real.

34
00:09:07.460 --> 00:09:11.620
- Here. Don Minu.
- Find anything out?

35
00:09:12.380 --> 00:09:17.700
There's no news from Stefano.
But I got this from Lucia.

36
00:09:42.620 --> 00:09:47.300
Tell Bellantone to get Lucia.

37
00:10:16.660 --> 00:10:19.660
Mico. come here.

38
00:10:27.260 --> 00:10:31.060
Are you tired?
A little bit?

39
00:10:31.300 --> 00:10:35.380
Everything's going to be fine.
don't worry. Okay?

40
00:10:45.940 --> 00:10:47.820
Lucia.

41
00:10:47.900 --> 00:10:50.020
Mico.

42
00:10:50.060 --> 00:10:53.340
Mico! C'mon. come here.

43
00:10:53.540 --> 00:10:57.300
- Come.
- All good? Let's go!

44
00:10:58.020 --> 00:11:00.180
Little guy!

45
00:11:00.300 --> 00:11:03.980
Hi. Shake my hand?
Good boy!

46
00:11:04.660 --> 00:11:06.860
Let me hear you bark like a dog.

47
00:11:08.260 --> 00:11:10.060
Louder.

48
00:11:10.140 --> 00:11:12.540
Well done.

49
00:11:12.620 --> 00:11:15.620
Were you waiting long?

50
00:11:16.180 --> 00:11:18.540
No.

51
00:11:23.900 --> 00:11:26.140
Don Minu...

52
00:11:32.740 --> 00:11:37.100
Bellantone's sons
picked up Lucia and the boy.

53
00:11:43.140 --> 00:11:45.580
Good.

54
00:11:47.020 --> 00:11:48.860
That's good.

55
00:11:56.460 --> 00:11:59.180
- We've arrived.
- There's a car.

56
00:11:59.660 --> 00:12:02.540
There are no animals?

57
00:12:04.620 --> 00:12:07.980
- Will you get the suitcase?
- I'll get it.

58
00:12:11.060 --> 00:12:13.820
Come on. Mico.

59
00:12:15.420 --> 00:12:18.060
Be careful.

60
00:12:20.580 --> 00:12:23.900
Watch out.
Get some rest. Lucia.

61
00:12:24.100 --> 00:12:25.900
Yes. thank you.

62
00:12:26.500 --> 00:12:28.820
Mico. come in.

63
00:12:31.460 --> 00:12:34.020
Let's go in.

64
00:12:47.660 --> 00:12:49.780
Domenico.

65
00:12:50.460 --> 00:12:52.700
Well?

66
00:12:56.660 --> 00:12:59.580
Relax. Lucia.

67
00:13:00.580 --> 00:13:04.180
If Stefano does as we say.
nothing will happen to you.

68
00:13:08.220 --> 00:13:11.300
You gonna open that door or not?

69
00:13:11.860 --> 00:13:14.020
- Stefano will get revenge.
- Sure...

70
00:13:14.220 --> 00:13:16.500
Move. get in there!

71
00:13:16.580 --> 00:13:19.580
Take it easy. Antonello!

72
00:13:19.780 --> 00:13:23.020
Calm down.
What are you worried about?

73
00:13:23.140 --> 00:13:25.780
Your father will understand.
calm down.

74
00:13:25.860 --> 00:13:30.220
Betraying Don Minu is the smartest
move for the Bellantone family.

75
00:13:30.420 --> 00:13:33.300
- You've done the right thing.
- I know.

76
00:13:33.540 --> 00:13:35.780
Don Minu is old.
the world's spinning backwards.

77
00:13:35.980 --> 00:13:38.660
if we don't fix it. we'll disappear.

78
00:13:38.860 --> 00:13:41.100
Right? What do you say. Palmiro?

79
00:13:41.580 --> 00:13:44.460
It's like you say.

80
00:13:45.580 --> 00:13:48.140
Let's go.

81
00:14:03.860 --> 00:14:08.780
If you love your wife.
you better stop the fucking brokers.

82
00:14:18.140 --> 00:14:20.660
- Lucia. are you okay?
- Ste'...

83
00:14:20.740 --> 00:14:22.460
Slut!

84
00:14:24.260 --> 00:14:26.300
The fuck you doing? Hitting my face?

85
00:14:29.900 --> 00:14:32.260
You wanna save them?

86
00:14:32.340 --> 00:14:34.500
You wanna save them?

87
00:14:34.580 --> 00:14:37.740
I'll slit your throat!
I'm going to kill you!

88
00:14:37.820 --> 00:14:40.180
Stop the fucking brokers.

89
00:14:42.060 --> 00:14:43.380
Bye. Stefano.

90
00:14:44.820 --> 00:14:47.780
- Wait!
- What was that?

91
00:14:48.580 --> 00:14:52.060
- We can stop the brokers.
- Yeah? How?

92
00:14:52.140 --> 00:14:56.460
- We can stop them.
- How? Tell me.

93
00:14:56.540 --> 00:14:59.620
- I know where the cargo is.
- Really?

94
00:14:59.820 --> 00:15:01.620
I know where the cargo is!

95
00:15:01.820 --> 00:15:04.900
My grandfather told me
how to trace it.

96
00:15:04.980 --> 00:15:07.540
Open the door. Gianpietro.

97
00:15:50.740 --> 00:15:54.740
I didn't think my sons
would betray Don Minu.

98
00:15:55.060 --> 00:15:58.620
At least let my son go.

99
00:16:02.500 --> 00:16:07.180
My sons were wrong.
but they're my blood.

100
00:16:07.860 --> 00:16:11.420
I can't abandon them.

101
00:16:11.500 --> 00:16:14.420
They'll slit your throats. one by one.

102
00:16:17.100 --> 00:16:21.100
Don Minu will make
the Bellantone family disappear.

103
00:16:50.660 --> 00:16:54.180
- Good to see you. Stefano.
- Thanks. let's go.

104
00:16:54.260 --> 00:16:58.580
- Pleased to see you.
- Pleasure's all mine.

105
00:16:58.660 --> 00:17:02.500
- Who's he?
- He's with me.

106
00:17:02.740 --> 00:17:06.740
- Alright. Get in the car.
- Thanks.

107
00:17:21.460 --> 00:17:25.060
- How are things here?
- They're good.

108
00:17:25.980 --> 00:17:30.260
What's new up there?
How's Don Minu?

109
00:17:31.020 --> 00:17:36.380
- He's good.
- I'm glad. Your wife and son?

110
00:17:40.260 --> 00:17:43.820
The boy's six now.

111
00:17:44.540 --> 00:17:48.460
Have you found the two brokers
who've got the shipment?

112
00:17:48.580 --> 00:17:50.940
We'll figure it out.
I've already spoken to a friend.

113
00:17:51.020 --> 00:17:53.540
- So. we know how?
- Of course.

114
00:18:00.180 --> 00:18:03.860
There's a woman. Amina.
she's the fixer's daughter.

115
00:18:04.100 --> 00:18:07.860
She works with him. they've got
an office down at the port.

116
00:18:07.980 --> 00:18:11.620
- How much longer?
- A few minutes. we're nearly there.

117
00:18:11.740 --> 00:18:17.220
Yasser. the father.
is the Lynwoods' fixer in Casablanca.

118
00:18:26.860 --> 00:18:30.540
In my heart. I'm praying for you.

119
00:18:36.860 --> 00:18:39.460
Here.

120
00:18:46.180 --> 00:18:48.980
- Amina?
- Yes?

121
00:18:50.980 --> 00:18:54.060
Can I help you?

122
00:18:57.860 --> 00:19:00.060
You have to come with us.

123
00:19:43.060 --> 00:19:45.540
I'm giving you what you want.

124
00:19:45.620 --> 00:19:49.340
- I'm giving you what you want.
- I don't get it.

125
00:19:49.380 --> 00:19:52.300
Now give me your word
of honor in front of him

126
00:19:52.380 --> 00:19:55.700
that you'll free Lucia and my son.

127
00:20:01.860 --> 00:20:05.100
- Word of honor.
- Are we clear?

128
00:20:07.060 --> 00:20:09.060
Yes.

129
00:21:18.180 --> 00:21:23.500
- Is this one or that one?
- It's this one.

130
00:21:23.700 --> 00:21:27.340
Okay. knock at the door.

131
00:21:29.780 --> 00:21:32.460
Say nothing.

132
00:21:36.860 --> 00:21:39.340
Hold on!

133
00:22:34.700 --> 00:22:37.700
I can't believe
we pulled that off.

134
00:22:37.780 --> 00:22:41.780
Yasser still has to ship it
to Calabria. He's good though.

135
00:22:48.540 --> 00:22:51.060
We make a good team. Em.

136
00:22:51.140 --> 00:22:53.460
Yes we are!

137
00:22:53.940 --> 00:22:58.300
But right now we've got
to get our stuff onto that ship.

138
00:23:08.460 --> 00:23:11.300
This way.

139
00:23:19.780 --> 00:23:22.260
Come in.

140
00:23:29.820 --> 00:23:34.620
It's comfortable.
you can find everything you need.

141
00:23:34.700 --> 00:23:39.700
The place is safe.
Nobody knows that you are here.

142
00:23:39.900 --> 00:23:42.460
My daughter will stop by
tomorrow morning.

143
00:23:42.660 --> 00:23:45.380
She will pick the money
for the customs officer.

144
00:23:45.580 --> 00:23:48.260
And we have to sort out
the necessary documents

145
00:23:48.460 --> 00:23:50.300
for the shipment to Gioia Tauro.

146
00:23:50.500 --> 00:23:52.940
We also need some medication.
It's called tetrabenazine.

147
00:23:53.260 --> 00:23:54.380
Can you get that?

148
00:23:54.580 --> 00:23:56.740
My daughter
will bring it to you tomorrow.

149
00:23:56.940 --> 00:24:00.980
- Thank you.
- I'll leave you alone. See you.

150
00:25:36.220 --> 00:25:39.060
I'm soaked.

151
00:25:54.380 --> 00:25:56.660
Fuck!

152
00:26:52.540 --> 00:26:55.860
Hey. Are you okay?

153
00:27:05.140 --> 00:27:07.460
I pissed myself.

154
00:27:18.580 --> 00:27:22.700
- No. I'll... I can do it.
- Don't worry.

155
00:27:28.140 --> 00:27:31.300
I'm fine. Em. don't worry.

156
00:27:36.020 --> 00:27:38.500
Come here.

157
00:27:40.620 --> 00:27:44.180
We can invest in research
and just sell everything we have.

158
00:27:44.380 --> 00:27:46.500
I couldn't sell Dad's business.

159
00:27:46.700 --> 00:27:51.500
The purpose of a family business
is to serve the family's interests.

160
00:27:53.260 --> 00:27:55.620
Right?

161
00:27:57.460 --> 00:28:00.980
What was Dad's number one rule?

162
00:28:02.740 --> 00:28:06.980
- Money solves everything.
- Exactly. kiddo.

163
00:28:27.220 --> 00:28:29.780
Hi. Amina. I'm Yasser's daughter.

164
00:28:32.780 --> 00:28:34.900
Chris.

165
00:28:34.980 --> 00:28:38.220
- Come in.
- Thank you.

166
00:28:43.940 --> 00:28:45.860
I'd like to see the shipment
before it leaves.

167
00:28:46.060 --> 00:28:47.660
Yeah. of course.

168
00:28:49.060 --> 00:28:54.580
Here's the... This is the money
for the Customs officer.

169
00:28:54.660 --> 00:28:58.060
I also have the medicine
you asked my father for.

170
00:28:58.260 --> 00:29:00.460
Thank you.

171
00:29:01.700 --> 00:29:04.820
Okay. we're all set.
I should be going.

172
00:29:05.020 --> 00:29:07.660
I'll go with you
in case you need anything.

173
00:29:07.860 --> 00:29:11.260
- Sure.
- That good with you?

174
00:29:12.340 --> 00:29:15.660
That's fine with me.

175
00:29:16.940 --> 00:29:21.220
- Go ahead.
- Okay. let's go.

176
00:29:37.860 --> 00:29:41.100
This is the old Medina.

177
00:29:41.180 --> 00:29:44.940
Your English is really good.

178
00:29:45.020 --> 00:29:48.580
- I studied in London.
- Really?

179
00:29:49.820 --> 00:29:55.100
It was the best time of my life.
I never wanted to come back.

180
00:29:57.060 --> 00:29:59.780
- Why did you?
- I did because of my dad.

181
00:29:59.900 --> 00:30:02.180
That was the deal.

182
00:30:02.260 --> 00:30:05.380
He let me study abroad and I had
to come back and work with him

183
00:30:05.580 --> 00:30:09.860
as soon as I was done.
so here I am.

184
00:30:13.340 --> 00:30:16.780
Are you an only child?

185
00:30:16.860 --> 00:30:20.020
Is it that obvious?

186
00:30:20.100 --> 00:30:24.100
No. I just... No.

187
00:30:24.740 --> 00:30:28.580
- Just starting conversation.
- Yeah. yeah.

188
00:30:29.260 --> 00:30:31.860
- Do you have kids?
- No.

189
00:30:34.020 --> 00:30:37.300
- Do you have kids?
- No. I don't. I'm single.

190
00:30:37.420 --> 00:30:40.140
Yeah. me too.

191
00:30:46.980 --> 00:30:51.140
Okay. this silence after saying
that we're single!

192
00:31:01.260 --> 00:31:04.420
- Hi. Dad.
- Hi. darling.

193
00:31:05.380 --> 00:31:08.460
- How are you enjoying Casablanca?
- It's good.

194
00:31:08.660 --> 00:31:10.580
Later go fix everything at the port.

195
00:31:11.140 --> 00:31:14.220
I have an appointment at Customs.

196
00:32:09.740 --> 00:32:12.620
Follow me.

197
00:32:22.700 --> 00:32:25.700
You wait for me here.

198
00:33:29.980 --> 00:33:32.700
You know. I've never been in love.

199
00:33:35.620 --> 00:33:37.580
In what sense?

200
00:33:37.780 --> 00:33:41.580
I'm thirty years old
and I've never been in love.

201
00:33:43.700 --> 00:33:45.500
What about that girl

202
00:33:45.700 --> 00:33:49.900
you brought to Thanksgiving
when we were in college?

203
00:33:50.820 --> 00:33:55.740
I liked her but...
I was scared.

204
00:33:56.940 --> 00:34:00.060
- Scared?
- Yeah.

205
00:34:01.740 --> 00:34:05.140
I could tell
you and Dad didn't like her

206
00:34:05.220 --> 00:34:09.180
and I knew it wasn't going to last
so I didn't want to...

207
00:34:10.420 --> 00:34:12.460
Yeah. that's all.

208
00:34:15.220 --> 00:34:18.060
We've got to get out more.

209
00:34:18.900 --> 00:34:22.380
- We could go out tonight.
- Yeah?

210
00:34:23.260 --> 00:34:28.460
Yeah. Amina's going to a party.
She said we should go.

211
00:34:29.580 --> 00:34:31.660
We should go.

212
00:34:32.300 --> 00:34:34.940
You sure?

213
00:34:35.100 --> 00:34:39.100
She couldn't take her eyes off you.
I was going to slap her.

214
00:34:40.340 --> 00:34:42.980
- Let's go.
- Okay.

215
00:38:23.980 --> 00:38:27.500
Fuck! Damn!

216
00:38:28.300 --> 00:38:29.940
Chris?

217
00:38:30.060 --> 00:38:32.740
Hate this fucking disease!

218
00:38:32.820 --> 00:38:35.700
Hey. are you okay?

219
00:38:37.300 --> 00:38:39.180
Damn!

220
00:38:39.260 --> 00:38:42.140
Chris...

221
00:38:45.460 --> 00:38:47.860
What's going on?

222
00:38:49.780 --> 00:38:53.700
- Chris? What's...
- Get away from me!

223
00:38:57.780 --> 00:38:59.700
Fuck!

224
00:39:00.740 --> 00:39:02.700
Fuck! Fuck! Fuck!

225
00:39:02.780 --> 00:39:05.100
- Dammit!
- Stop!

226
00:39:07.100 --> 00:39:08.740
Stop it!

227
00:39:09.460 --> 00:39:11.500
It's not fair.

228
00:39:11.660 --> 00:39:13.460
It's not fair!

229
00:39:13.700 --> 00:39:16.740
It's not fair! It's not fair!

230
00:39:17.100 --> 00:39:19.380
Fuck!

231
00:39:20.900 --> 00:39:22.860
Fuck!

232
00:39:29.460 --> 00:39:31.780
I can't...

233
00:39:39.180 --> 00:39:41.380
We can't...

234
00:39:49.140 --> 00:39:51.460
I'm sorry.

235
00:40:03.420 --> 00:40:05.820
I'm sorry.

236
00:40:43.740 --> 00:40:45.940
What are you doing here in the street?

237
00:41:36.620 --> 00:41:38.820
Come on.

238
00:41:39.820 --> 00:41:42.740
Are you okay?

239
00:41:42.900 --> 00:41:45.980
Where have you been?

240
00:41:46.180 --> 00:41:49.700
Amina called me.
What happened?

241
00:41:50.140 --> 00:41:52.420
Chris!

242
00:41:54.260 --> 00:41:57.140
What happened?

243
00:42:02.300 --> 00:42:05.060
I'm dying.

244
00:42:24.420 --> 00:42:27.220
You should take 'em.

245
00:42:36.180 --> 00:42:38.380
I'm tired.

246
00:42:39.300 --> 00:42:41.140
Hey.

247
00:42:41.300 --> 00:42:45.780
Look. I think it's better
if I go to the port alone. okay?

248
00:42:47.100 --> 00:42:49.300
I wanna make sure everything's okay.

249
00:42:49.460 --> 00:42:52.620
- Make sure the ship sets off at noon.
- Sure.

250
00:42:56.660 --> 00:43:00.940
Then I want you to get
the first flight back to New Orleans.

251
00:43:01.180 --> 00:43:04.580
And I'll finish up in Calabria.

252
00:43:09.780 --> 00:43:12.340
I want to come with you.

253
00:43:17.700 --> 00:43:20.500
I'll see you when I get home.

254
00:43:22.660 --> 00:43:26.300
We'll do like we said. we're going
to do everything together.

255
00:43:28.460 --> 00:43:30.580
Are you mad at me?

256
00:43:34.140 --> 00:43:35.820
No. kiddo.

257
00:44:10.300 --> 00:44:12.580
No. kiddo.

258
00:44:26.220 --> 00:44:30.540
Where are you?
Check nobody is following you.

259
00:44:39.580 --> 00:44:42.740
Thanks. bye.

260
00:44:43.180 --> 00:44:45.220
Our truck is arriving soon.
Miss Lynwood.

261
00:45:21.580 --> 00:45:24.180
